ACL -> Access control list 

Basic commands 
1. Check if ACL is supported 
   mount | grep acl 

2. View ACL of a file/direcotry 
   getfacl filename 

3. Set ACL for a user 
   setfacl -m u:alice:r file.txt 

4. Set ACL for a group 
   setfacl -m g:developers:rw file.txt 

5. Remove ACL
   setfacl -x u:alice file.txt 

6. Default ACL on a direcotry
   setfacl -a -m u:alice:rw project/